Sounds¶

It is possible to play specific sounds in the PetBlocks plugin when a certain action appears.

The metadata of the sounds are not stored in the database and get used by the referenced stored engine. Basically you can change the used sound in the config.yml and every players pet uses the new sounds.

Configuration and Samples¶

  • Pet sounds are played for every nearby player per default. This can be changed in the config.yml.

config.yml:

pet:
  design:
    sounds-other-players: true
  • The configuration values for sounds always consist of the following values:

config.yml:

name: 'NAME_OF_THE_SOUND_VERSION_DEPENDENT'
volume: 1.0
pitch: 1.0

Name: Name of the played sound. Be careful when you configure this as the names of the sounds changed between 1.8.9 and 1.9.0 and changed again between 1.12.2 and 1.13.0. You can find a list of sounds below.

Volume: The volume of sound. This is mostly used in Minecraft for configuring the amount of blocks this sound is audible. You can set volume to 0.0 to disable the sound. This values ranges from 0 - 100000

Pitch: This changes the pitch value of the sound. This value ranges from 0.0 to 2.0.

Engine sounds¶

  • The engine of a pet forces 2 major sounds being played when a pet gets used.

Ambient: Sound occasionally being played when the pet chooses to.

Walking: Sound being played when the pet moves.

config.yml:

engines:
  1:
   sound:
      ambient:
        name: 'PIG_IDLE'
        volume: 1.0
        pitch: 1.0
      walking:
        name: 'PIG_WALK'
        volume: 1.0
        pitch: 1.0

This configuration plays the PIG_IDLE sound randomly and the sound PIG_WALK when the pet moves.

You might have noticed that these sounds are from 1.8.9 and not available in the latest server version. The PetBlocks plugin automatically translates the default sounds in the config.yml. Not more or less.
